> I'm tempted to go completely

22:34.587 --> 22:38.890
nuts for all the things I like,

22:38.891 --> 22:42.961
like pies, beans, and chips.

22:42.962 --> 22:45.063
Cheese beano, I don't know what

22:45.064 --> 22:49.401
that is, but I kind of want it.

22:49.402 --> 22:50.736
Ooh, sausage roll.

22:50.737 --> 22:53.972
I do like a good sausage.

22:53.973 --> 22:57.909
I order the fish and
chips and some haggis.

22:57.910 --> 23:03.949
Haddock battered and floating, a

23:03.950 --> 23:06.585
drift in a sea of life-giving

23:06.586 --> 23:14.586
oil as it Bobs like Noah's
ark bringing life in all its

23:15.828 --> 23:17.128
infinite variety.

23:17.129 --> 23:18.664
In tube form in this case.

23:18.665 --> 23:20.599
If you don't like chopped up

23:20.600 --> 23:26.705
liver and lungs and all
that stuff, believe me.

23:26.706 --> 23:34.706
The curry sauce sets you right.

23:35.882 --> 23:41.487
Guy Fieri in a kilt,
but what the hey.

23:41.488 --> 23:45.857
I'm pretty sure god
is against this.

23:45.858 --> 23:53.799
Oh, yeah, definitely.

23:53.800 --> 23:54.365
That's good.

23:54.366 --> 23:56.668
Doesn't eat well with a fork.

23:56.669 --> 24:02.307
You really have to pick this up.

24:02.308 --> 24:03.056
So ashamed.

24:19.492 --> 24:23.328
Oh, yeah.

24:23.329 --> 24:26.865
Clean living.

24:26.866 --> 24:34.866
That's really one of
life's great pleasures.

24:34.874 --> 24:36.174
Don't let them tell
you otherwise.

24:36.175 --> 24:39.611
They're lying about you, Mr.

24:39.612 --> 24:40.679
Haggis.

24:40.680 --> 24:45.183
There was no other reviled
food on earth than haggis.

24:45.184 --> 24:49.588
It's ingredients are no
more unusual or bizarre or

24:49.589 --> 24:53.191
unappetizing than any
hot dog you ever ate.

24:53.192 --> 24:54.760
How many anal glands are
in a chicken nugget?

24:54.761 --> 24:57.362
I don't know and I'm not

24:57.363 --> 24:59.030
suggesting there are anal glands

24:59.031 --> 25:04.069
in a chicken nugget, but would

25:04.070 --> 25:05.303
you be surprised if there were?

25:05.304 --> 25:07.273
Back to you, wolf.

25:25.491 --> 25:32.263
Heading north out of
Glasgow, Scotland quickly

25:32.264 --> 25:34.566
becomes something else.

25:34.567 --> 25:38.069
A savagely beautiful harsh, but

25:38.070 --> 25:41.740
absolutely mesmerizing landscape

25:41.741 --> 25:42.974
that seems to have changed not

25:42.975 --> 25:44.743
at all for thousands,
even millions of years.

25:44.744 --> 25:49.648
And across loch Marie and only

25:49.649 --> 25:51.983
accessible by boat, one of the

25:51.984 --> 25:58.256
great isolated
estates, letter U.

25:58.257 --> 26:01.860
It's the favorite retreat
of my friend, Adrian Gill.

26:01.861 --> 26:05.496
More widely known as a Gill.

26:05.497 --> 26:08.934
He's the much feared and widely

26:08.935 --> 26:11.302
followed restaurant critic for

26:11.303 --> 26:15.140
the "London Sunday times,"

26:15.141 --> 26:17.843
author, traveler, and one of the

26:17.844 --> 26:20.712
finest essayists of our time.

26:20.713 --> 26:22.614
Letter U. As it stands today was

26:22.615 --> 26:24.015
built as a shooting lodge.

26:24.016 --> 26:26.451
Deer stalking like they do here

26:26.452 --> 26:28.153
is something from another era,

26:28.154 --> 26:34.125
but it persists in places like

26:34.126 --> 26:36.628
this which both protect and
cull deer populations.

26:36.629 --> 26:40.298
If you are, like us, of course,

26:40.299 --> 26:43.969
two murderous aristocrats
looking to put venison on the

26:43.970 --> 26:47.072
table, you need help,
professional help.

26:47.073 --> 26:49.240
Stephen Miller has been working

26:49.241 --> 26:51.142
here for eight seasons now, both

26:51.143 --> 26:53.078
protecting the animals who live

26:53.079 --> 26:55.480
on it and helping people like us

26:55.481 --> 26:57.649
in the arduous and delicate task

26:57.650 --> 27:02.020
of sneaking up on them.

27:02.021 --> 27:05.657
We would as gentlemen of leisure

27:05.658 --> 27:08.994
require a cook and Adrian has

27:08.995 --> 27:13.164
recommended a well-suited woman

27:13.165 --> 27:16.334
who excels at this
Scottish game cookery.

27:16.335 --> 27:19.738
For dinner, it's grouse.

27:19.739 --> 27:25.610
Shot, then hung until the
already funky game bird gets

27:25.611 --> 27:26.012
pleasingly ripe.

27:26.013 --> 27:27.578
The birds are rubbed inside and

27:27.579 --> 27:35.086
out with salt and pepper, some

27:35.087 --> 27:36.922
fresh thyme jammed
in the cavity.

27:36.923 --> 27:38.356
Bread sauce is a must.

27:38.357 --> 27:43.461
We don't do this in America,
but here it's essential.

27:43.462 --> 27:46.364
Basically it's milk simmered

27:46.365 --> 27:48.399
with flavoring agent like nutmeg

27:48.400 --> 27:55.473
and bay leaf and then thickened
with raspings of bread.

27:55.474 --> 28:01.880
Grouse barded with bacon,
then roasted in the oven.

28:01.881 --> 28:04.382
They are moved to rest.

28:04.383 --> 28:07.652
Game stock is added and the

28:07.653 --> 28:08.887
sauce reduced, topped with water

28:08.888 --> 28:16.888
cross along side with
parsnips and beet root.

28:18.731 --> 28:19.364
So explain what we're eating,

28:19.365 --> 28:20.265
because this is as
classic as it gets?

28:20.266 --> 28:21.499
This is specifically Scottish.

28:21.500 --> 28:23.769
This is a grouse, which is the

28:23.770 --> 28:27.472
only truly wild game
bird in Britain.

28:27.473 --> 28:33.078
They're the most highly
prized as a sporting bird.

28:33.079 --> 28:34.145
They're the most difficult to

28:34.146 --> 28:35.646
shoot, but more importantly

28:35.647 --> 28:37.448
they're the most prized to eat.

28:37.449 --> 28:40.418
This bread sauce
thing, what is that?

28:40.419 --> 28:43.588
Bread sauce, you have to
grow up here to love this.

28:43.589 --> 28:47.092
It is like pottage.

28:47.093 --> 28:47.426
It's soft.

28:47.427 --> 28:53.431
It's a very old dish, but it
goes very well... grouse,

28:53.432 --> 28:56.601
they're a very gamey meat.

28:56.602 --> 29:00.972
It's a very grown-up taste that

29:00.973 --> 29:05.443
is slightly repellant, but

29:05.444 --> 29:08.313
within that, it is
particularly Al alluring.

29:08.314 --> 29:08.714
Right.

29:08.715 --> 29:12.283
There is something also
sexual about it that people

29:12.284 --> 29:13.284
don't often talk about.

29:13.285 --> 29:16.154
Right, right.

29:16.155 --> 29:17.222
So good.

29:17.223 --> 29:19.791
I'm going to a
vegetarian school.

29:19.792 --> 29:26.965
My parents sent me to a
vegetarian boarding school, and

29:26.966 --> 29:29.901
for nine years, the year after I

29:29.902 --> 29:31.069
left, I was a vegetarian.

29:31.070 --> 29:35.974
Nine years as a vegetarian,
that's unthinkable to me.

29:35.975 --> 29:37.708
Then I decided not to be.

29:37.709 --> 29:39.410
I made the decision if I was

29:39.411 --> 29:41.346
going to eat meat again, then I

29:41.347 --> 29:43.381
had to be prepared to
do the whole business.

29:43.382 --> 29:45.316
Right.

29:45.317 --> 29:46.985
You've got to be accountable.

29:46.986 --> 29:49.320
For all of it.

29:49.321 --> 29:51.056
For all of it.

29:51.057 --> 29:54.325
So I started with the fish and

29:54.326 --> 29:56.327
getting the guts and gutting it.

29:56.328 --> 29:57.595
You want to eat it?

29:57.596 --> 29:58.663
Come and kill it.

29:58.664 --> 30:02.567
You go, well, then I
have to do that as well.

30:02.568 --> 30:09.007
When I started doing it,
it was like coming home.

30:09.008 --> 30:17.008
And that's the thing
with being on the hill.

30:25.191 --> 30:27.025
Until the 19th century, the

30:27.026 --> 30:29.027
Scottish highlands were seen by

30:29.028 --> 30:32.197
many as a mysterious, hostile,

30:32.198 --> 30:34.065
and dangerous land, populated

30:34.066 --> 30:37.702
when populated at all by scary

30:37.703 --> 30:44.409
ass barbarians, tribes so
ferocious, so extravagant in

30:44.410 --> 30:46.411
their violence and toughness

30:46.412 --> 30:49.948
that even in the Roman legions

30:49.949 --> 30:52.951
decided not to mess with them,

30:52.952 --> 30:54.285
hoping to keep them out of the

30:54.286 --> 30:56.387
way of civilized society.

30:56.388 --> 30:58.223
Later hunting estates like this

30:58.224 --> 31:05.230
were home to farmers who
scrounged a living by growing

31:05.231 --> 31:05.497
potatoes.

31:05.498 --> 31:13.104
The highland clans
later by newer money.

31:13.105 --> 31:15.006
Today around half the land in

31:15.007 --> 31:23.007
Scotland is owned by
fewer than 500 people.

31:25.351 --> 31:30.922
It's seductive as well.

31:30.923 --> 31:33.091
Who wouldn't do this,
if they could?

31:33.092 --> 31:38.429
Enjoy this kind of rugged

31:38.430 --> 31:41.299
solitude from a warm,
inviting 17th century lodge.

31:41.300 --> 31:47.105
Play a little snooker, enjoy
a single malt or two, the

31:47.106 --> 31:53.678
substantial game meal, maybe
another whiskey perhaps,

31:53.679 --> 31:56.647
contemplate the mysteries of the

31:56.648 --> 31:57.882
universe under the sky and then

31:57.883 --> 32:04.322
to sleep in the arms of

32:04.323 --> 32:06.624
Morpheus, then to rise in the

32:06.625 --> 32:10.195
morning as bringer of death.

32:10.196 --> 32:12.897
Stephen and Adrian keep calling

32:12.898 --> 32:16.367
it the hill, but that ain't
no hill I've ever seen.

32:16.368 --> 32:19.637
It's a behemoth, an endless

32:19.638 --> 32:22.640
range of behemoths, one mountain

32:22.641 --> 32:30.641
way giving away to a moor, then

32:31.984 --> 32:37.688
another, then
another, then more.

32:37.689 --> 32:39.824
It's a daunting hike.

32:39.825 --> 32:41.326
The climb gradual, then steep.

32:41.327 --> 32:46.731
The footing ranging from
rocky to spongy and wet.

32:46.732 --> 32:47.398
Mile after mile.

32:47.399 --> 32:50.535
Me trying to look cool, make it

32:50.536 --> 32:52.003
seem like this is nothing

32:52.004 --> 32:56.975
unusual, but really I'm dying.

33:12.858 --> 33:16.361
We walked the
highlands for hours.

33:16.362 --> 33:20.365
Our stalker Stephen finally
identifies a red stag of

33:20.366 --> 33:23.268
suitable age and size, one ready

33:23.269 --> 33:25.103
in parlance to be
taken off the hill.

33:25.104 --> 33:27.938
Getting in a range without

33:27.939 --> 33:29.974
scaring them off, however,
is another challenge.

33:29.975 --> 33:32.410
We need to circle around the

33:32.411 --> 33:33.744
mountain to close the distance.

33:33.745 --> 33:41.745
There's not a lot I can do.

33:43.722 --> 33:51.722
So we go slowly.

33:52.498 --> 33:59.337
Just pretend we're
hikers at the moment.

33:59.338 --> 34:00.071
Bobble hat.

34:00.072 --> 34:00.638
What?

34:00.639 --> 34:03.241
If you put a bobble hat on,

34:03.242 --> 34:11.242
the deer think you're a hiker.

34:19.024 --> 34:23.860
Can you see the antlers?

34:23.862 --> 34:24.362
Yeah.

34:31.303 --> 34:31.915
Get down.

34:40.978 --> 34:48.978
Stay down, stay down.

34:52.491 --> 35:00.491
Dig in nice and steady.

35:03.302 --> 35:04.270
Take your time.

35:37.536 --> 35:39.069
That's a nice stag.

35:39.070 --> 35:40.004
Ten points.

35:40.005 --> 35:41.172
Is that good?

35:41.173 --> 35:45.743
He was never going
to get any better.

35:45.744 --> 35:50.281
Do you want to use your knife?

35:50.282 --> 35:53.252
♪

36:22.881 --> 36:29.220
For shooting your first
red stag in Scotland.

36:29.221 --> 36:32.823
You'll get blooded.

36:32.824 --> 36:33.058
Oh.

36:33.059 --> 36:41.059
Best if you close your eyes.

36:42.133 --> 36:43.067
Ah.

36:43.068 --> 36:45.736
Oh, okay.

36:45.737 --> 36:47.905
And the rule is you
have to leave it on.

36:47.906 --> 36:50.107
Yeah.

36:50.108 --> 36:52.077
All day.

37:09.328 --> 37:09.495
♪

37:09.496 --> 37:10.261
You going, chaps?

37:10.262 --> 37:16.867
As getting vehicles up here
would be both physical and

37:16.868 --> 37:18.336
destructive they use highland

37:18.337 --> 37:20.605
ponies to retrieve
the stalked deer.

37:20.606 --> 37:24.208
They are bred to be strong
and trained to do this work.

37:24.209 --> 37:27.345
They will likely make it
back sooner than we will.

37:27.346 --> 37:29.814
Thanks, chaps.

37:29.815 --> 37:32.283
We'll catch you
around at some point.

37:32.284 --> 37:32.784
See ya.

37:36.522 --> 37:42.827
Good boys through.

37:42.828 --> 37:45.796
I thought coming up my legs

37:45.797 --> 37:47.031
burning, I can't wait until that

37:47.032 --> 37:49.300
nice easy downhill walk back,

37:49.301 --> 37:54.372
but as I soon find out, the
walk down is even harder.

37:54.373 --> 37:56.674
Knees screaming, face crusted

37:56.675 --> 37:59.043
with dry blood, I'm looking

37:59.044 --> 38:01.312
forward to a warm fire, a strong

38:01.313 --> 38:07.486
whiskey and spot good
country ass cooking.

38:49.528 --> 38:53.297
So venison stew with wine?

38:53.298 --> 38:56.967
They always marinate
Juniper and all of that.

38:56.968 --> 38:58.636
Super simple.

38:58.637 --> 38:59.137
Okay.

38:59.138 --> 38:59.937
We'll do that.

38:59.938 --> 39:00.438
♪

39:12.984 --> 39:14.084
The venison is seasoned with

39:14.085 --> 39:15.886
salt and pepper and Rosemary

39:15.887 --> 39:21.091
seared in duck fat and
then into the oven.

39:21.092 --> 39:22.893
A pan sauce made from the Fawn,

39:22.894 --> 39:25.295
red wine and deep game stock,

39:25.296 --> 39:26.997
sweetened with currentant jelly

39:26.998 --> 39:29.133
and finishing with a nod of

39:29.134 --> 39:35.506
whole butter and served with

39:35.507 --> 39:43.507
clap shot, basically mashed turnips and potatoes.

39:47.453 --> 39:47.985
That's it.

39:47.986 --> 39:49.186
That's the end of the season.

39:49.187 --> 39:50.455
Hugely the girls will be killing

39:50.456 --> 39:52.657
it, and you start
killing the girls.

39:52.658 --> 39:53.658
Have you traditionally where

39:53.659 --> 39:58.763
there's the leather mask to the

39:58.764 --> 40:00.431
stag and you... and you send

40:00.432 --> 40:03.834
them notes beforehand
saying I'm watching you.

40:03.835 --> 40:11.835
I know where you live.

40:22.187 --> 40:24.188
We deserve this.

40:24.189 --> 40:25.523
We've worked for it, huh?

40:25.524 --> 40:28.559
Yeah.

40:28.560 --> 40:29.894
Literally the greatest feat

40:29.895 --> 40:33.464
of strength in my entire life.

40:33.465 --> 40:35.132
Never in my entire life have I

40:35.133 --> 40:37.635
done anything so remotely

40:37.636 --> 40:40.505
physical over a sustained
period of time.

40:40.506 --> 40:41.371
Really?

40:41.372 --> 40:42.640
Never.

40:42.641 --> 40:43.173
Look how well.

40:43.174 --> 40:45.810
At no point previously in my

40:45.811 --> 40:48.145
life would I have
been able to do it.

40:48.146 --> 40:49.880
Thank you, guys.

40:49.881 --> 40:51.582
Here's to the best
of health, folks.

40:51.583 --> 40:52.917
All the best.

40:52.918 --> 40:53.684
Good shot.

40:53.685 --> 41:01.685
I say to a place for ramblers.

41:01.927 --> 41:03.562
A lot safer now that
we're not on our land.

41:24.382 --> 41:26.050
I came to Scotland this time

41:26.051 --> 41:28.452
to shoot an animal in the heart,

41:28.453 --> 41:30.120
to take part, to be fully

41:30.121 --> 41:34.925
culpable in a practice nearly
as old as these hills.

41:34.926 --> 41:36.460
You walk this country stalking

41:36.461 --> 41:37.962
an animal across the rocks and

41:37.963 --> 41:39.764
wet Heather, you feel little has

41:39.765 --> 41:41.298
changed from how your distant

41:41.299 --> 41:43.133
ancestors must have searched for

41:43.134 --> 41:47.905
their food with a rifle,
with a spear, with a club.

41:47.906 --> 41:50.274
I drag my knuckles up a hill and

41:50.275 --> 41:52.042
like my ape-like predecessors

41:52.043 --> 41:56.747
return tired, happy
and covered in blood.

41:56.748 --> 41:58.148
Everything changes.

